@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{pass-extras.el} extends the @samp{pass} package, which provides an Emacs interface to the Unix @samp{pass} password manager. While @samp{pass} already offers browsing and copying of password entries, this package adds several capabilities that streamline common workflows:

@itemize
@item
Opening the URL associated with a password entry while simultaneously copying the password to the clipboard (@ref{Browsing entries}).
@item
Generating passwords of various types and copying them to the clipboard with automatic clearing (@ref{Generating passwords}).
@item
Storing external key files into the password store and exporting entries back out (@ref{Key management}).
@item
Unlocking @samp{git-crypt} repositories using keys stored in @samp{pass} (@ref{Git-crypt integration}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{pass} and @samp{password-generator}.

